1. Create a comparison table listing at least 5 key differences between traditional WAN and SD-WAN, focusing on how data is routed, managed, and secured.
=>Aspect                     Traditional WAN                                                                      SD-WAN
Data Routing           Static routing or manual policy-based (e.g., MPLS)           Dynamic, application-aware intelligent routing (based on real-time performance)"
Management             Decentralized, device-by-device CLI/config                      Centralized controller/orchestrator with policy automation
Security               Often relies on perimeter firewalls/VPNs                       Integrated zero-trust, segmentation, and encryption with cloud integration"
Link Usage            Primarily private links (MPLS) with backup                          Hybrid (MPLS + broadband + 4G/5G) with active-active load balancing
Scalability & Agility      Slow provisioning (weeks/months), hardware-dependent          Rapid overlay deployment, software-defined policies for cloud/direct internet access"

